items.title: LOVE IS THE SEARCH FOR A LOST PARADISE
items.description:
https://letterboxd.com/film/love-is-the-search-for-a-lost-paradise/

𝐎 𝐀𝐌𝐎𝐑 É 𝐀 𝐁𝐔𝐒𝐀 𝐏𝐎𝐑 𝐔𝐌 𝐏𝐀𝐑𝐀Í𝐒𝐎 𝐏𝐄𝐑𝐃𝐈𝐃𝐎 (2024)

As imagens deste filme foram captadas de forma casual durante uma caminhada matinal pela Praia de Pitangueiras, no Guarujá. Saí com minha handycam e comecei a gravar algumas cenas, mas, enquanto filmava, eu já sabia que aquele material poderia se transformar em um curta-metragem.

Li essa frase em um livro de Alexander Lowen: “O amor é a busca por um paraíso perdido”, e, a partir dessas imagens, combinadas com alguns renders em 3D, quis expressar essa ideia na tela.

The footage for this film was captured casually during a morning walk along Pitangueiras Beach in Guarujá. I went out with my handycam and started recording some scenes, but while filming, I knew this material could become a short film.

I read this phrase in a book by Alexander Lowen: *”LOVE IS THE SEARCH FOR A LOST PARADISE”*, and from these images, combined with some 3D renders, I wanted to express that on the screen.

https://gabrielkoi.com/film

items.description:
MOTHERBOARD, a 2023 film, becoming my most well-known work, being screened in multiple spaces around the world — in Brazil, Spain, the United States, and the Philippines.

"Motherboard" is an experimental film that dives into the intersection of technology and consciousness, exploring the subtle boundary between the human and the digital. In this journey within the circuit, reality blends with the digital, challenging the understanding of existence, while the contrast of the human intertwines with the artificial, echoing the cry of this new consciousness.

I found out that when i visit other people's dreams, i assume a body with a crystallized skin"

"In this hidden chamber, the powerful process of Autopoiesis" was appropriate by beings that frequently call their acts glorious and progressive, the summit were divided and a great risk was generated. Although, in a process that self-create, the capacity of comprehension is always updated, which practically makes the process of total appropriation impossible."

"Some says that the Human Race is the fifth race to walk the "Path", having contact with the "Intelligence". They Say they had four other races before us, with their societies, cultures and values. items.title: the flash tries to be god
the man in the dead machine
items.description:
High on a slope in New Guinea
the Grumman Hellcat
lodges among bright vines
as thick as arms.

In 1943, the clenched hand of a pilot
gloves itself in the cockpit
and then,
with a gesture of gentleness,
touches the throttle.

He rises into his war
and the vines forget him.

Now the long grasses
run fingers over a body
they can only imagine,
and the vines
wrap themselves lovingly
around the metal bones.

Somewhere among those green shadows
is the shape of a man
who said good-bye to his mother
for the last time
and then went to war.

items.title: Dr. Lollipop
items.description:
S.E.E.D. Entity 1


Description:
A spaced labyrinth, populated by grotesque creatures, is captured by a high-angle lens — fused within the very eyeball of the creature that observes the defendant: Dr. Lollipop.

Dwelling in a living, mobile laboratory, he merges into a thousand organisms and viscous structures, generating endless creatures. In an intertwining of flesh and bytes, wires cover condemned and sublime bodies. A vast, suspended, viscous, repulsive being.

Attention!

Dr. Lollipop presents:
— Within a hybrid space, the body is my vehicle for experiences and also my anchor in reality. Technological tensions articulate within me as extensions, amplifying my voice and presence. Through this, I connect with other distant avatars, sharing stories and forging bonds of survival.

His physical body is the laboratory — a silent witness to the vicissitudes of the Third World. Inside, his aqueous being rediscovers itself in an omnipresent heterotopia, without fixed form. In this virtual context, each creature is born from sensors and personas, within a vast spectrum of chaos where multiple avatars create their own fictions, realities, and fantasies. These avatars traverse real and virtual ecosystems, generating movements, cultures, and subcultures.

The experiment manifests not as an abstract intellectual exercise but as a direct affectation of the gaze — reinventing notions of identity and reality. Within imagination, the experiment speculates on the correlation between mind and world, opening a gap that elaborates the absolute: an infinite and mutable space.

The absolute is thinkable — yet it is chaos, contingency, an open field of infinite possibilities. A speculation about the world beyond human perception reveals a desire for transcendence. Subjectivity is traversed by cosmic forces, using art as a medium to access expanded knowledge.

Dr. Lollipop again:
— Each creature is born by convergence, in a hybrid space that transcends the tangible and anchors itself in reality through my own embodiment.

Remember: in the confluence between the real and the imaginary, chaos dances with order like a ballerina star. To decipher the absolute, one must accept the enigma of existence and seek truth in the interstices — where the threads of the visible intertwine with the vertiginous shadows of the unknown.

And never forget the side effects.

Dr. Lollipop disintegrates and exits.

items.description:
The Tao of Physics is a book written by Austrian physicist Fritjof Capra, first published in 1975. The work seeks to show the parallels between the advances of modern physics (especially quantum theory, relativity, and particle physics) and Eastern mystical traditions, such as Taoism, Buddhism, and Hinduism.

Capra argues that, although they may seem like very different fields — Western science and Eastern spiritual philosophies — both describe reality as an interconnected whole, dynamic and in constant transformation. Quantum physics, for example, reveals a universe where the boundaries between matter and energy, observer and observed, are fluid — something that recalls the mystical principles of unity and interdependence.

items.title: Magic Feet

Life can be seen as a personal bag, where we store everything we go through. Each experience, each encounter, each emotion is like an object placed inside. Often, we don’t even realize what we’re collecting—small joys, silent pains, hidden lessons.

This bag is unique to each person, impossible for anyone else to open. Only the one carrying it knows its weight, its shape, and the mystery of what lies within. That’s why it’s always a surprise: when we least expect it, life opens a hidden compartment and reveals something we didn’t even remember keeping.

And maybe that’s the beauty of life itself: learning to look inside our own bag, recognizing what’s already there, letting go of what weighs us down, and valuing what truly matters. Because in the end, this bag is also our identity—a reflection of who we were, who we are, and who we still have the chance to become.

items.title: The Balloon
items.description:
Connections change, and people enter and leave our lives in an instant.

The bond between people is not something static; it lives and breathes, nourished by presence, conversations, and shared moments. When these elements fade, even unintentionally, the connection weakens. Sometimes, it only takes a single moment—a longer silence, a message that never arrives, a meeting that doesn’t happen—to realize that some people are moving in different directions.

Perhaps one of the most important lessons is to understand that life is made of cycles, and some bonds serve their purpose and come to an end so that others can begin. Accepting this is making room for new connections, new stories, and new joys.

And sometimes, we are the ones who take that step, letting go of those who no longer belong in our lives. It can happen suddenly, but each farewell creates space for unexpected encounters, which can arrive as quickly as others have left. It all begins this way: with an idea that quietly blooms and, little by little, takes shape in the material world. When we allow ourselves to feel the environment and simply be present, life unfolds before us effortlessly. And in that flow, people and moments come and go like the tides, always leaving room for the magic of what is yet to come.

CYBERIA XEQUE MATE é um evento performativo organizado pela SEED, coletivo interdisciplinar de artistas que atuam na interseção entre arte, tecnologia e linguagem digital. Realizado no Rio de Janeiro, o evento propõe a fusão entre festa, performance e jogo, erguendo um tabuleiro vivo de xadrez ao centro da pista, que se transforma em um campo de encontro e ritualização, onde o raciocínio, o corpo e o som se entrelaçam em uma dramaturgia expandida.

A instalação central — composta por uma mesa, um tabuleiro e duas cadeiras — convida o público a participar de partidas de xadrez ao longo da noite, assumindo o papel de jogadores num território sensível de experimentação tática e performativa.

As atrações sonoras do evento são responsáveis por compor a trilha sonora imersiva de um jogo em andamento, atravessando o espaço com ritmos e atmosferas que tensionam o tempo e o corpo. 
E aqui, mesmo quem não joga, joga.

The "Have Fun Pump" initiative showcases the power of Zora's new secondary market system, which brings liquidity and long-term value to creators and collectors. For GnarsDAO, this was an exciting moment as one of our videos became the first-ever video token to utilize this system. Through Zora's protocol, a portion of the mint fees was used to bootstrap liquidity on Uniswap, creating a dynamic and permissionless market for collectors to trade the token even after the mint ended.

This means that collectors who missed the minting window can now buy the token on the open market, with each transaction contributing to GnarsDAO's earnings through Secondary Rewards. This system ensures that the token's value evolves with demand, creating lasting opportunities for both creators and collectors. It’s a fun and innovative way to keep the Nounish energy alive, even after the initial mint period has ended.

items.description:
And closing out the sound lineup, an unprecedented b2b is coming soon: @b4dvi and @tha______is join forces, blending their influences with percussive rhythms that range from house to techno.

badvi is the musical project of Victor Hugo, a DJ and beatmaker born and raised in the outskirts of São Paulo's East Zone.
